    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted on the basis that quasi-static ambient testing is conservative for structural yield prediction and that the primary regulatory QoIs are fully covered. The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support a Medium assurance level conclusion that the FEA framework reliably predicts ASTM F1717 compression-bending performance of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
